ğŸ“¦ Installation & Setup
Prerequisites
Node.js (v16+)

MongoDB Atlas account

Cloudinary account

Razorpay test account

Resend API key

ğŸ”§ Local Development
Clone the repository

bash
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/trenzzo.git
cd trenzzo
Backend Setup

bash
cd backend
npm install
cp .env.example .env

# Fill in your environment variables

npm run dev
Frontend Setup

bash
cd frontend
npm install
cp .env.example .env

# Fill in your environment variables

npm run dev
Access the application

text
Frontend: http://localhost:5173
Backend: http://localhost:5000
ğŸ” Environment Variables
Backend (.env)
env

# Server

PORT=5000
NODE_ENV=development

# Database

MONGODB_URI=your_mongodb_connection_string

# JWT

JWT_SECRET=your_jwt_secret_key
JWT_EXPIRE=7d

# Cloudinary

CLOUDINARY_CLOUD_NAME=your_cloud_name
CLOUDINARY_API_KEY=your_api_key
CLOUDINARY_API_SECRET=your_api_secret

# Razorpay (Test Mode)

RAZORPAY_KEY_ID=your_razorpay_key_id
RAZORPAY_KEY_SECRET=your_razorpay_key_secret

# Resend (Email OTP)

RESEND_API_KEY=your_resend_api_key
RESEND_FROM_EMAIL=notifications@yourdomain.com

# Frontend URL

FRONTEND_URL=http://localhost:5173
Frontend (.env)
env
VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:5000/api
VITE_SOCKET_URL=http://localhost:5000
VITE_RAZORPAY_KEY_ID=your_razorpay_key_id
VITE_CLOUDINARY_CLOUD_NAME=your_cloud_name
ğŸ’³ Razorpay Test Mode
The platform uses Razorpay in test mode for payment processing. Test mode allows you to simulate transactions without real money.

Test Card Details
text
Card Number: 4111 1111 1111 1111
Expiry: Any future date (MM/YY)
CVV: Any 3 digits
OTP: 1234 (if prompted)
Test UPI ID
text
success@razorpay
Test NetBanking
text
Any bank - use "success" as credentials
Test Wallet
text
Use any amount - transaction will be marked as successful
âš ï¸ Important: All transactions in test mode are simulated. No real money is transferred.

ğŸ“š API Documentation
Authentication Endpoints
Method Endpoint Description Access
POST /api/auth/register User registration Public
POST /api/auth/login User login Public
POST /api/auth/send-otp Send OTP via email Public
POST /api/auth/verify-otp Verify OTP Public
Category Endpoints
Method Endpoint Description Access
GET /api/category Get all categories Public
POST /api/category Create category Admin
PUT /api/category/:id Update category Admin
DELETE /api/category/:id Delete category Admin
Product Endpoints
Method Endpoint Description Access
GET /api/product Get products Public
POST /api/product Create product Seller
PUT /api/product/:id Update product Seller
DELETE /api/product/:id Delete product Seller/Admin
Order Endpoints
Method Endpoint Description Access
POST /api/order Create order User
GET /api/order/my-orders Get user orders User
GET /api/order/seller Get seller orders Seller
PUT /api/order/:id/status Update order status Seller/Admin
Full API Documentation â†’

